BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Family Night Out – Townie Summer Kick-off
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260513T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260513T200000
UID:ai1ec-150025-95470@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Family Night Out is a monthly block part designed for easy\, l
 ow-pressure community connection right in the heart of downtown.On the sec
 ond Wednesday of every month thru October from 4:30-8PM\, Kirkwood Ave in 
 front of the Monroe County Public Library transforms into a share dining r
 oom and open-air gathering space. Bring your people\, grab takeout from pa
 rticipating local restaurants offering special deals\, and sit down togeth
 er at long family-style tables set right in the middle of the street.Along
  the block you’ll find local art vendors\, community partners hosting ha
 nds-on activities\, and a rotating lineup of buskers filling the air with 
 live music. The Front Porch Trailer bring casual lawn games and extra spac
 e to hang out\, play\, and linger a little longer.It’s part dinner\, par
 t street fair\, part neighborhood hangout. Come eat\, wander\, play\, and 
 stay awhile.
LOCATION:Library Plaza\, 300 Block of East Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/family-night-out-townie-summer-kick-off/?instan
 ce_id=95470
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
