DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Finn: A New Musical- 
 At the PB&J Cafe\,” on stage May 1-17 at the Waldron Auditorium.From the
  creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a heartwarming musical 
 adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing up. As he prepares t
 o join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake the feeling that he
 ’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he discovers a colorfu
 l fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to sparkle\, sing\, and d
 ance. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, friendship\, and ad
 venture\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for all ages!PB&J Cafe: 
 A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young theatergoers will enjo
 y a meal during the performance and leave with autographs from their favor
 ite characters.
LOCATION:Waldron Arts Center (122 S Walnut St)
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/finn-a-new-musical-at-the-pbj-cafe-2/?instance_
 id=90581
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cinderella
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260517T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260517T163000
UID:ai1ec-149724-95461@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:The classic tale of Cinderella like you’ve never seen it bef
 ore. Featuring Rodgers & Hammerstein’s most beloved songs—including 
 “Ten Minutes Ago” and “Stepsister’s Lament” This production is f
 ull of heart\, humor\, and a little bit of magic.YOUR ARE INVITED to join 
 us for a timeless fairy tale. Rodgers & Hammerstein’s Cinderella brings 
 a fresh\, witty\, and romantic heart to the classic story.Follow the journ
 ey of a kind-hearted young woman who\, despite being mistreated by her soc
 ial-climbing stepfamily\, never loses her spirit or her dreams. With the h
 elp of a delightfully magical Fairy Godmother\, a pumpkin is transformed i
 nto a carriage\, and Cinderella is swept away to the Royal Ball. Beyond th
 e glass slipper and the midnight deadline\, this production focuses on the
  power of kindness and the “impossible” becoming possible through a lu
 sh\, Broadway-style score and a story that proves you don’t need magic t
 o change your world. Just a little courage.
LOCATION:Little Theatre of Bedford Indiana\, 1704 Brian Ln Way\, Bedford
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/cinderella-2/?instance_id=95461
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
